01:31:07.052 --> 01:31:09.543
Matthews, over here!

01:31:11.056 --> 01:31:13.684
We're gonna stop the train
before Rockdale.

01:31:13.684 --> 01:31:17.092
Closest is...
the Harris Mill Junction.

01:31:17.092 --> 01:31:21.190
Contact the railroad. Tell them to make
out like it's a routine emergency inspection.

01:31:21.190 --> 01:31:24.100
Have Bronsky bring his men
up in choppers from the south..

01:31:24.100 --> 01:31:26.866
Get all the passengers off the train,
and I don't want any slip-ups.

01:31:26.866 --> 01:31:29.840
We'll be there as soon as we can.
Caldwell, you come with us.

01:31:29.840 --> 01:31:31.739
Steward, what do you want to do?

01:31:31.739 --> 01:31:35.007
This has been a nerve-shattering
experience. I'd like to go home.

01:31:35.814 --> 01:31:37.441
Take him anywhere he wants.

01:31:37.441 --> 01:31:39.949
Okay, men, grab your rifles.
Let's move it.!

01:31:39.949 --> 01:31:43.044
Caldwell, your shells.

01:31:43.788 --> 01:31:44.508
Let's go.!

01:31:45.957 --> 01:31:49.654
- What does he think I'm gonna do with this?
- Blow the tires out on the train.

01:31:50.428 --> 01:31:51.690
Thanks for everything.

01:31:54.032 --> 01:31:55.431
My pleasure.

01:31:56.434 --> 01:31:58.732
Goddamn it.!
Caldwell, get out here.!

01:31:58.732 --> 01:32:02.261
If there's ever anything
that you need...

01:32:06.010 --> 01:32:07.340
don't call me.

01:32:10.080 --> 01:32:12.207
Don't let 'em get you killed.

01:32:16.119 --> 01:32:19.213
Take it easy, killer.
Stay loose.

01:32:35.172 --> 01:32:37.333
Where'd you like to go, fella?

01:32:37.333 --> 01:32:38.738
Well..

01:32:41.210 --> 01:32:43.405
I left myJag in Kansas City.

01:32:58.027 --> 01:33:00.257
I don't know, Frank,
but that's what they said.

01:33:00.257 --> 01:33:02.524
Everybody off
at the Harris Mill Junction.

01:33:02.524 --> 01:33:06.694
Everybody off?
Okay, I'll tell my crew.

01:33:27.022 --> 01:33:31.254
- Why are they stoppin' the train?
-I don't know, sir. Tryin' to get some security check here.

01:33:31.254 --> 01:33:33.521
That's the damnedest thing
I ever heard!

01:33:33.521 --> 01:33:36.462
- They want us to get off the train?
- Yeah.

01:33:37.933 --> 01:33:40.299
- Hey, there's the police!
- Watch your step. Watch your step.

01:33:40.299 --> 01:33:42.666
- Well, I'll be...
- Come on, get back!

01:33:42.666 --> 01:33:45.672
You guys are just totally uncontrollable.
You know that?

01:33:56.050 --> 01:33:57.608
- The police are here.
- What?

01:33:57.608 --> 01:34:00.279
The porters are askin' everyone
to get off the train.

01:34:02.389 --> 01:34:04.084
Are they?

01:34:06.860 --> 01:34:10.023
Keep moving towards the clearing, please.

01:34:12.132 --> 01:34:16.228
This is a routine investigation.
None of you is in danger.

01:34:17.805 --> 01:34:21.502
Please cooperate with us so we can
complete our investigation quickly...

01:34:21.502 --> 01:34:24.703
and get you back aboard
and on your way.

01:34:28.401 --> 01:34:29.702
Please keep moving...

01:34:37.323 --> 01:34:38.847
Excuse me.

01:34:41.561 --> 01:34:43.426
Yeah, excuse me.

01:34:47.634 --> 01:34:51.070
- Everybody off, please, Mr. Devereau.
- Yes. What's happening here, Conductor?

01:34:51.070 --> 01:34:54.163
We're not sure. We got a call from
the police wanting everyone evacuated.

01:34:54.163 --> 01:34:56.902
- Maybe it's a bomb scare.
- A bomb scare?

01:34:56.902 --> 01:34:59.705
- Then we'd better get off.
- I certainly am.

01:35:37.615 --> 01:35:39.515
Stay with her.

01:35:39.515 --> 01:35:43.178
Cover us from the window. We're gonna
start the engine and take this thing to Rockdale.

01:35:43.178 --> 01:35:47.748
Hey, what are you doin'? Everybody's gone.
What are you doin' with those rifles?

01:35:52.063 --> 01:35:54.122
You bastards!

01:35:56.967 --> 01:35:59.731
Everyone's off, Chief,
except our boy.

01:36:01.472 --> 01:36:03.099
Hold it right there, Devereau!

01:36:54.456 --> 01:36:56.253
- Shit!
- Take it easy, killer.

01:36:56.253 --> 01:36:58.486
What are you doing here?

01:36:59.762 --> 01:37:01.923
What's going on?
Who's in charge here?

01:37:01.923 --> 01:37:03.589
Would you get down!

01:37:05.400 --> 01:37:07.391
What did you come back here for?

01:37:09.938 --> 01:37:13.465
- Uh... I forgot your wallet.
- Oh, some thief you are.

01:37:14.510 --> 01:37:17.138
- Is that your old lady Hilly?
- Yeah.

01:37:20.214 --> 01:37:21.704
Okay, follow me.

01:37:33.294 --> 01:37:35.319
- Start the engine.
- We can't do that.

01:37:36.297 --> 01:37:38.857
You, move, start it.

01:38:10.764 --> 01:38:13.665
Mr. Devereau.
Mr. Devereau!

01:38:23.510 --> 01:38:25.273
Guido, come with me!

01:38:50.703 --> 01:38:53.365
Keep your foot on the pedal.

01:39:13.291 --> 01:39:15.486
- Come on!
- Where are we going?

01:39:15.486 --> 01:39:17.619
We're getting off at the next stop.

01:39:20.431 --> 01:39:22.991
- What are you doing?
- This is combat.

01:39:51.995 --> 01:39:53.519
Watch out for the engineer.

01:39:57.534 --> 01:39:59.024
Sit!

01:40:29.799 --> 01:40:32.233
- Are you all right?
- Yes.

01:40:32.233 --> 01:40:34.292
How about Grover?

01:40:38.140 --> 01:40:40.131
Are you all right?

01:40:40.131 --> 01:40:42.302
- Is it over?
- Shit.!

01:41:10.338 --> 01:41:11.828
Look out!

01:41:15.443 --> 01:41:18.879
- You okay?
- Yeah, I'm all right.

01:41:22.649 --> 01:41:24.583
Just give me one more pass.

01:41:47.608 --> 01:41:50.771
Just give me one clear shot.

01:42:25.445 --> 01:42:27.276
- What happened?
- Don't look. Don't look!

01:42:32.918 --> 01:42:35.944
All right, get theJunction
on the radio.

01:42:35.944 --> 01:42:38.319
Tell them they've got
a runaway train.

01:42:39.091 --> 01:42:41.286
Hey, we're comin'
into the station.

01:42:55.340 --> 01:43:00.175
George, why didn't we stop?
What's going on here?

01:43:00.175 --> 01:43:02.645
I'm not sure, but I don't think
that there's anyone in the engine.

01:43:02.645 --> 01:43:05.012
- No driver?
- That's right.

01:43:05.012 --> 01:43:07.141
Oh, God!

01:43:07.141 --> 01:43:09.709
Whiney cut
all the emergency cords.

01:43:09.709 --> 01:43:11.721
What are we gonna do?

01:43:13.891 --> 01:43:17.019
- Well, we have to find some way to get to the engine.
- How?

01:43:19.063 --> 01:43:20.553
The roof?

01:43:21.999 --> 01:43:24.832
I think so.
Come on!

01:43:35.279 --> 01:43:37.509
- How's it going?
- They don't believe us.

01:43:37.509 --> 01:43:41.744
Look, the engineer is probably anxious
to bring the train in on schedule.

01:43:44.053 --> 01:43:46.214
This is Chief Donaldson.
Who's this?

01:43:46.214 --> 01:43:49.087
This is Jerry Jarvis.
I'm the assistant controller.

01:43:49.087 --> 01:43:51.150
Assistant? Get me your boss.

01:43:51.150 --> 01:43:55.357
Uh, he's out to lunch, but I'm sure
I can handle any problem you might have.

01:43:55.357 --> 01:43:59.026
It's not my problem. You've got a dead
engineer and a runaway train...

01:43:59.026 --> 01:44:02.196
- that's gonna hit Chicago in 15 minutes.
- What are you gonna do about it?

01:44:02.196 --> 01:44:05.400
All right, I'll check
with the signal towers.

01:44:05.400 --> 01:44:07.909
But, uh, you see,
it's impossible.

01:44:07.909 --> 01:44:10.878
If the engineer is dead,
who's driving the train?

01:44:20.656 --> 01:44:23.181
- What's happening?
- Hey, you all right?

01:44:23.181 --> 01:44:26.318
- Listen, is there any way...
- Holy moley! The killer!

01:44:26.318 --> 01:44:28.192
- No, he's okay.
- Listen to me.

01:44:28.192 --> 01:44:31.130
Is there any way to get to the engine
without going over the roof?

01:44:31.130 --> 01:44:33.464
There ain't no way to get to the engine,
period!

01:44:33.464 --> 01:44:36.993
- Why are we goin' so fast?
- Because there's no one driving this train.

01:44:36.993 --> 01:44:40.530
- Impossible. It would stop.
- Does this look as if we're stopping?

01:44:41.343 --> 01:44:44.540
No, the hell it don't.!
I better go pull the emergency cord.

01:44:44.540 --> 01:44:46.979
The emergency cords
have been cut.

01:44:46.979 --> 01:44:48.778
Damn hippies!

01:44:51.219 --> 01:44:55.588
I received a report from the signal towers.
They see no engineer in the cabin.

01:44:55.588 --> 01:44:57.521
Great. Now you've got the facts.

01:44:57.521 --> 01:45:00.584
Throw one of those switches
and have the train run off.

01:45:00.584 --> 01:45:04.927
That's the problem.
All the tracks are computer programmed.

01:45:04.927 --> 01:45:07.729
Switching the Silver Streak would only
cause a collision with another train.

01:45:07.729 --> 01:45:11.465
Then what the hell are you gonna do?
There are people riding on that train.

01:45:11.465 --> 01:45:13.370
Oh, no.

01:45:13.370 --> 01:45:14.999
You see, the standard procedure...

01:45:14.999 --> 01:45:18.102
in such an emergency
would be to derail the train.

01:45:18.102 --> 01:45:19.942
Derail it?
In the middle of the yard?

01:45:20.948 --> 01:45:25.281
Yes. Actually,
I can't take that responsibility.
Uh, I'd better get my boss.

01:45:25.281 --> 01:45:28.321
You better do something,
you idiot, because in 10 minutes...

01:45:28.321 --> 01:45:30.379
you're gonna have
200 tons of locomotive

01:45:30.379 --> 01:45:33.984
smashing through Central Station
on its way to Marshall Fields!

01:45:38.064 --> 01:45:41.500
- Where are we going?
- If you wanna stop this train, you got to follow me!

01:45:45.972 --> 01:45:48.304
Hey, Jack,
have you seen Benny?

01:45:48.304 --> 01:45:50.935
Uh, yeah, yeah. I saw him
in the coffee shop, Jerry.

01:46:00.085 --> 01:46:02.883
Now what we have to do
is uncouple the cars.

01:46:02.883 --> 01:46:05.947
You gotta pull up that bar,
turn it to the left.

01:46:05.947 --> 01:46:09.620
When they pull apart, they will
bust open the air pressure lines...

01:46:09.620 --> 01:46:12.892
and the brakes will clamp on throughout
the train, then you can jump on back.

01:46:13.565 --> 01:46:15.863
- But that's dangerous.!
- Impossible, man.

01:46:16.769 --> 01:46:18.361
Grab hold of my belt.

01:46:18.361 --> 01:46:20.305
- What are you gonna do?
- Guess!

01:46:26.878 --> 01:46:30.541
- Have you seen Benny?
- Well, if it isn't the little Caesar of the railroad.

01:46:30.541 --> 01:46:33.583
- Have you seen Benny!
- No. No!

01:46:33.583 --> 01:46:35.015
Try next door.

01:47:17.159 --> 01:47:18.251
What's the matter?

01:47:18.251 --> 01:47:20.989
The Silver Streak is a runaway.
What do we do?

01:47:22.331 --> 01:47:24.458
Jesus! It's gonna be here
in four minutes!

01:47:40.816 --> 01:47:42.749
Your attention, please.

01:47:42.749 --> 01:47:45.752
May I have
your attention, please.

01:47:45.752 --> 01:47:49.779
You are requested to walk to
the nearest exit as quickly as possible.

01:47:49.779 --> 01:47:51.348
Please do not run.

01:47:51.348 --> 01:47:54.554
Walk as quickly
as possible to the nearest exit.

01:47:55.363 --> 01:48:00.426
People waiting for the arrival
of the Silver Streak on track five...

01:48:00.426 --> 01:48:02.663
are requested to vacate
that area immediately.

01:48:24.858 --> 01:48:30.262
This is an emergency. Please continue
to the nearest exit where a station security...

01:48:51.518 --> 01:48:56.045
Exit as quickly as possible.
You must leave the building..

01:50:18.669 --> 01:50:22.002
We did it! We made it!
We made it, man! Whoo!

01:50:24.408 --> 01:50:25.898
Holy shit!

01:50:29.280 --> 01:50:32.249
Hello, Chicago! Hello!

01:50:32.249 --> 01:50:34.181
Gotta drink to that!

01:50:50.166 --> 01:50:53.533
I don't know about you,
but next time I'm gonna take the bus.

01:50:53.533 --> 01:50:56.800
Maybe I'm crazy,
but it looks as if it's grinning.

01:50:56.800 --> 01:50:59.774
Yeah, like the cat
who swallowed the canary.

01:50:59.774 --> 01:51:02.174
- Where's Grover?
- I don't know.

01:51:10.386 --> 01:51:13.582
Take it easy, killer.
Stay loose!

01:51:15.490 --> 01:51:17.287
What's he doing?

01:51:17.287 --> 01:51:19.020
He's crazy.

01:51:20.062 --> 01:51:22.553
Crazy? He's got the right idea.

01:51:22.553 --> 01:51:25.532
- Let's get outta here and go to a park.
- A park?

01:51:25.532 --> 01:51:28.035
Yeah. I want
to lie back on the grass...

01:51:28.035 --> 01:51:30.765
and have you teach me
some more about gardening.

